'''''Star Wars: Visionaries''''' is a [[Wikipedia:Graphic novel|graphic novel]] published by [[Dark Horse Comics]]. It features 11 stories written and drawn by concept artists who worked on [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']]. ''Visionaries'' was edited by [[Jeremy Barlow]] and contains an introduction by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler]], who came up with the concept and pitched it to Dark Horse.<ref name="Insider 82">{{InsiderCite|82|Drawn by the Force}}</ref>

The comics constituting ''Visionaries'' are also collected in ''[[Star Wars Omnibus: Wild Space Volume 2]]''.

==Publisher's summary==
''They've been responsible for some of the most dazzling and awe-inspiring visuals ever put to film, and now the concept artists behind the Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'' bring their considerable talents to comics. The gifted minds of the Lucasfilm art department and the visual effects powerhouse Industrial Light & Magic come together to tell their own ''Star Wars'' tales in this compilation of short stories. Given free reign to explore any and every aspect of the ''Star Wars'' universe, each artist offers a new twist or a deeper view into that galaxy far, far away''.

''Nowhere else will you find a more pure or more different look at George Lucas' enduring creation than through the eyes of the ''Star Wars: Visionaries''.''

==Contents==
*"[[Old Wounds]]" by [[Aaron McBride]]
*"[[The Artist of Naboo]]" by [[Erik Tiemens]]
*"[[Wat Tambor and the Quest for the Sacred Eye of the Albino Cyclops]]" by [[Michael Murnane]]
*"[[Sithisis]]" by [[Derek Thompson]]
*"[[Entrenched]]" by [[Alex Jaeger]] with [[M. Zachary Sherman]]
*"[[The Fourth Precept]]" by [[Stephan Martiniere]]
*"[[Prototypes]]" by [[Robert E. Barnes]]
*"[[Imperial Recruitment]]" by [[Feng Zhu]]
*"[[Deep Forest]]" by [[Sang Jun Lee]]
*"[[Celestia Galactica Photografica]]" by [[Ryan Church]]
*"[[The Eyes of Revolution]]" by [[Warren Fu]]

A story titled "[[In a Future, Far, Far Away...]]" by [[Iain McCaig]] was proposed for inclusion, but was never completed due to his obligations on ''Revenge of the Sith''.<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=posts/56657555|board=Literature|thread=Lostworlds & Lost Words: Cancelled Media|user=ColeFardreamer|date=2020-05-18|archiveurl=https://archive.md/s36cX}}</ref>

